div.h2: Segment Selector GDT Linear Address Resolution
div.p: Hardware performs CPL/DPL check on every memory access
Hardware Rule (every memory access): Access granted iff max(CPL, RPL) DPL

ul.li: CPL = Current Privilege Level = low 2 bits of CS
RPL = Requested Privilege Level = low 2 bits of selector
DPL = Descriptor Privilege Level = bits 6:5 of access byte Not a software check enforced in MMU silicon
